  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nAdd support for a step value in `range`.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nThis is possible in a Solidity for loop, and it's possible in a Python `range` which our syntax closely mimics.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nUse standard [Python syntax](https://docs.python.org/3.8/library/stdtypes.html#range) where the 3rd argument to `range` is the step value. If omitted, it is assumed to be `1`.  In the bytecode, where we currently perform `ADD 1` change it to `[ADD/SUB] [STEP]`.\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nShouldn't create any issues, as currently we raise an exception if a step value is given.\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
